headline: Why The Narrative Around Handelsbanken (OM:SHB A) Is Shifting On Mixed Analyst Targets And Risks
summary: The latest update to Svenska Handelsbanken’s model nudges fair value from SEK 133.73 to SEK 134.80, a small move that still matters if you care about where the share price sits versus analysts’ targets. This shift fits into a broader split in opinion, with some banks edging targets higher toward the mid SEK 140s while at least one has turned more cautious on the shares.
